Below is a production-grade discovery and audit plan to enumerate all automation mechanisms in a large Jira Data Center instance.
This is structured for completeness, repeatability, and cluster safety.

Scope assumption: enterprise-scale Jira DC (multi-node), multiple marketplace apps, custom scripts, and legacy artifacts.


---

0. Define Automation (Audit Definition)

Before scanning, standardize what qualifies as automation:

Automation = any deterministic logic that modifies state, enforces rules, or triggers actions without direct user intervention at execution time.

Includes:

Workflow logic

Listeners

Scheduled jobs

Scripted fields

UI dynamic logic

REST-triggered logic

Cluster services

External systems triggering Jira

Database-level jobs

Mail handlers

Notification hooks



---

1. Instance-Wide App & Module Inventory

1.1 Enumerate Installed Apps

Export:

UPM app list

Version numbers

Licensing state


Critical apps to inspect deeply:

ScriptRunner for Jira

Power Scripts for Jira

Jira Service Management

Jira Software


Reason: 80–90% of automation in DC lives in marketplace apps.


